Duke Defeats North Carolina 75-68 in ACC Final to Reach NCAA Tournament

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-03-13T19:44:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/duke-defeats-north-carolina-75-68-in-acc-final-to-reach-ncaa-tournament.html
  Duke University  beat the University
of North Carolina 75-58 to win the  Atlantic Coast Conference 
championship for a third straight year and claim a berth in
college basketball’s national men’s tournament.  Defending national champion and fifth-ranked Duke has a 94-
30 mark in 34 visits to the National Collegiate Athletic
Association tournament and will be chasing a fifth title this
year. The first round is scheduled for March 15 and 16.  Duke has now won the ACC tournament a record 19 times,
including 10 occasions since 1999. The Blue Devils and the
sixth-ranked  Tar Heels  have a combined 36 ACC titles and have
played 11 times for the championship, with North Carolina
winning six.  Nolan Smith led the Blue Devils with 20 points at the
Greensboro Coliseum in Greensboro,  North Carolina , today.  Duke  improves to 30-4 this season while North Carolina,
which finished the regular season atop the ACC standings with a
14-2 record, drops to 26-7.  The NCAA will reveal the 68 selections for the national
tournament in a broadcast on CBS that begins at 5 p.m. New York
time today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dex McLuskey in  Dallas   at
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 